Class KbFunctionImpl

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.cyc.kb.KbFunction, com.cyc.kb.KbIndividual, com.cyc.kb.KbObject, com.cyc.kb.KbTerm, com.cyc.kb.Relation

    public class KbFunctionImpl
extends RelationImpl
implements com.cyc.kb.KbFunction
    A KBFunction object is a facade for a #$Function-Denotational in the Cyc KB. A N-ary function is a many-one relation, between the N-tuple of the domain elements to a range element. Functions can be used to create "non-atomic terms" or #$CycLClosedNonAtomicTerm. The class provides a method to create new functional terms, which can in turn be used in other assertions, just as constants are.

    A new function is by default made a #$ReifiableFunction in the underlying Cyc Knowledge Base. A future version of the API will support un-reifiable functions.

      • findOrCreate

        public static KbFunctionImpl findOrCreate(String nameOrId)
                                   throws com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException,
                                          com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        Find or create a KBFunction object named nameOrId. If no object exists in the KB with the name nameOrId, one will be created, and it will be asserted to be an instance of #$Function-Denotational. If there is already an object in the KB called nameOrId, and it is already a #$Function-Denotational, it will be returned. If it is not already a #$Function-Denotational, but can be made into one by addition of assertions to the KB, such assertions will be made, and the object will be returned. If the object in the KB cannot be turned into a #$Function-Denotational by adding assertions (i.e. some existing assertion prevents it from being a #$Function-Denotational), a KBTypeConflictExceptionwill be thrown.
        Parameters:
        nameOrId - the string representation or the HLID of the #$Function-Denotational
        Returns:
        a new KBFunction
        Throws:
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException

If cycObject cannot be turned into a #$Function-Denotational by adding assertions (i.e. some existing assertion prevents it from being a #$Function-Denotational, a KBTypeConflictExceptionwill be thrown.

      • findOrCreate

        public static KbFunctionImpl findOrCreate(String nameOrId,
                          com.cyc.kb.KbCollection constraintCol)
                                   throws com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException,
                                          com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        Find or create a KBFunction object named nameOrId, and also make it an instance of constraintCol in the default context specified by KBAPIDefaultContext#forAssertion(). If no object exists in the KB with the name nameOrId, one will be created, and it will be asserted to be an instance of both #$Function-Denotational and constraintCol. If there is already an object in the KB called nameOrId, and it is already both a #$Function-Denotational and a constraintCol, it will be returned. If it is not already both a #$Function-Denotational and a constraintCol, but can be made so by addition of assertions to the KB, such assertions will be made, and the object will be returned. If the object in the KB cannot be turned into both a #$Function-Denotational and a constraintCol by adding assertions, a KBTypeConflictExceptionwill be thrown.
        Parameters:
        nameOrId - the string representation or the HLID of the #$Function-Denotational
        constraintCol - the collection that this #$Function-Denotational will instantiate
        Returns:
        a new KBFunction
        Throws:
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbTypeException
        com.cyc.kb.exception.CreateException
